            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I don't think this makes much sense - it'd just make it more likely for people to end up in import hell.\r\n\r\nFYI, the endpoint name doesn't even need to match the function name - this is just a default that works in many cases. Also, it is very common to use blueprints where you'd actually generate a url for `someblueprint.someendpoint`. Again, using the actual functions there would likely result in import hell."
