            "updated_at": "2017-02-21T22:29:09Z",
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I was not aware of an completely independent endpoint mapping distinct from the routing; so far I've only used routing decorators.\r\nDifferent blueprints could probably be accounted for by e.g. passing them as parameter as well\u2026\r\nThe possible ambiguity should not be much of a problem if the resulting URL leads to identical function calls upon request, and if someone wants to prevent ambiguity, they could always use the string variant, which I did not suggest to abandon."
